Indexo el genoma con minimap2:
minimap2 -d Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.dna.primary_assembly.mmi Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.dna.primary_assembly.fa.gz

Mapeo las lecturas de cada muestra contra el genoma de referencia:
minimap2 -ax splice Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.dna.primary_assembly.mmi sample_A.fastq --splice-flank yes --junc-bonus 10 -o sample_A.sam

Summary de los mapeos:
samtools flagstat sample_A.sam

ConversiÃ³n de los sam:
SAM --> sorted BAM:
samtools view -bS sample_A.sam | samtools sort -o sample_A.bam

BAM --> BAM.BAI:
samtools index sample_A.bam

BAM --> BED:
bamToBed -bed12 -i sample_A.bam > sample_A.bed

FLAIR correct
flair correct -q sample_A.bed -g Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.dna.primary_assembly.fa -f Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.115.chr.okok.gtf --output sample_A

FLAIR collapse
flair collapse --gtf Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.115.chr.okok.gtf -g Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.dna.primary_assembly.fa -q sample_A_all_corrected.bed -r sample_A.fastq --output sample_A --stringent --check_splice --generate_map

FLAIR quantify
flair quantify -r Resutados/quantify/reads_manifest_A.tsv -i sample_A.isoforms.fa --isoform_bed sample_A.isoforms.bed
